### 2. Builder Pattern with Ordered Method Chaining

```typescript
type NoNameBuilder = {
    setName: <Name extends string>(name: Name) => HasNameBuilder<Name>;
    setAge: never; // Can't call setAge before setName
    build: never;  // Can't call build yet
};

type HasNameBuilder<Name extends string> = {
    setName: never; // Can't call setName again
    setAge: <Age extends number>(age: Age) => HasNameAndAgeBuilder<Name, Age>;
    build: never;   // Can't call build yet
};

type HasNameAndAgeBuilder<Name extends string, Age extends number> = {
    setName: never; // Can't call setName again
    setAge: never;  // Can't call setAge again
    build: () => { name: Name, age: Age };
};

const builder: NoNameBuilder = {
    setName(name) {
        return {
            setName: () => { throw new Error("Can't set name twice") },
            setAge(age) {
                return {
                    setName: () => { throw new Error("Can't set name now") },
                    setAge: () => { throw new Error("Can't set age now") },
                    build: () => ({ name, age })
                };
            },
            build: () => { throw new Error("Must set age before building") }
        };
    },
    setAge: () => { throw new Error("Must set name first") } as never,
    build: () => { throw new Error("Must set name and age first") } as never
};

// Example usage:
const validBuild = builder.setName('Alice').setAge(30).build(); // ✓
console.log(validBuild); // { name: 'Alice', age: 30 }

const invalidOrder = builder.setAge(30).setName('Alice').build(); // ✗ Compile error
const missingAge = builder.setName('Alice').build(); // ✗ Compile error
const missingName = builder.setAge(30).build(); // ✗ Compile error
```

### Key Features:

1. **Route Type**:
   - `ExtractPathParams` recursively extracts all `:param` segments from the path
   - `ValidateParams` ensures the params object has exactly the required keys
   - Provides clear error messages when params don't match

2. **Builder Pattern**:
   - Uses a state machine pattern with different builder types
   - Each method returns a new builder type with only the allowed next steps
   - Attempting to call methods out of order results in compile-time errors
   - The `build` method is only available after all required steps are completed

Both solutions leverage TypeScript's advanced type system to enforce these constraints at compile time.

